'''Leirfjord''' is a [[List of municipalities of Norway|municipality]] in [[Nordland]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]].  It is part of the [[Helgeland]] [[Districts of Norway|traditional region]].  The administrative centre of the municipality is the village of [[Leland, Norway|Leland]].  Other villages in Leirfjord include [[Bardalssj<U+00F8>en]] and [[Sund<U+00F8>y]].  The large [[Helgeland Bridge]] is partly located in the municipality, connecting it to [[Alstahaug]] and the town of [[Sandnessj<U+00F8>en]].

==General information==
The municipality of Leirfjord was established on 1 July 1915 when it was separated from the municipality of [[Sandnessj<U+00F8>en|Stamnes]].  Initially, the municipality had 2,003 residents.  In 1945, a small part of [[Nesna]] (population: 45) was merged into Leirfjord.  On 1 January 1964, Leirfjord (population: 1,936) was merged with the southern part of [[Nesna]] (population: 580) and the parts of [[Tj<U+00F8>tta]] on the island of [[Alsta]] (population: 180) to form a new, larger municipality of Leirfjord.<ref>{{cite web|first=Dag|last=Jukvam|publisher=[[Statistics Norway|Statistisk sentralbyr<U+00E5>]]|title=Historisk oversikt over endringer i kommune- og fylkesinndelingen|year=1999|url=http://www.ssb.no/emner/00/90/rapp_9913/rapp_9913.pdf|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

===Name===
The municipality is named after the [[Leirfjorden]]. The old name of the [[fjord]] was probably just ''Leiri'', derived from the name of the river ''Leira'', which has its mouth in the end of the fjord. The river name is derived from the word ''leirr'' which means "[[clay]]".<ref name="snl">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/Leirfjord|title=Leirfjord|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2012-01-10}}</ref>

===Coat-of-arms===
The coat-of-arms is from modern times (1992). The arms show a green branch [[cross]] on a gold background.  It symbolizes [[forestry]] and [[agriculture]] in the municipality.  The arms were designed by Jarle E. Henriksen from [[Sandnessj<U+00F8>en]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leirfjord.kommune.no/index.asp?startID=&topExpand=&subExpand=&strUrl=//applications/system/publish/view/showobject.asp?infoobjectid=1003546&menuid=1002411&startmenuid=1000444|title=Leirfjord|accessdate=2008-11-23|publisher=Leirfjord kommune|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

===Churches===
The [[Church of Norway]] has one parish ''(sokn)''  within the municipality of Leirfjord.  It is part of the  [[List of churches in Nordland#Nord-Helgeland prosti|Nord-Helgeland]] [[deanery]] in the [[Diocese of S<U+00F8>r-H<U+00E5>logaland]].

